revisions.description: Version 5: Changed the MAX-ACCESS of bayStackUnitConfigIndex to read-only.
Version 4: Added spb value for bayStackUnitConfigRearPortAdminMode and bayStackUnitConfigRearPortOperMode.

bayStackConfigExpectedStackSize.name: bayStackConfigExpectedStackSize
bayStackConfigExpectedStackSize.description: The expected stack size. A unit that expects to be standalone would use a value of 1.

bayStackConfigStackErrorNotificationInte.name: bayStackConfigStackErrorNotificationInterval
bayStackConfigStackErrorNotificationInte.description: This objects controls the frequency with which bsnStackConfigurationError notifications are generated.

bayStackConfigStackErrorNotificationEnab.name: bayStackConfigStackErrorNotificationEnabled
bayStackConfigStackErrorNotificationEnab.description: This objects controls whether bsnStackConfigurationError notifications are generated.

bayStackConfigStackRebootUnitOnFailure.name: bayStackConfigStackRebootUnitOnFailure
bayStackConfigStackRebootUnitOnFailure.description: This object controls whether to reboot any unit in a stack whose stack ports do not go logically up.

bayStackUnitConfigTable.name: bayStackUnitConfigTable
bayStackUnitConfigTable.description: This table contains per-unit configuration data for a stack.

bayStackUnitConfigEntry.name: bayStackUnitConfigEntry
bayStackUnitConfigEntry.description: An entry of configuration data for a stacked unit.

bayStackUnitConfigIndex.name: bayStackUnitConfigIndex
bayStackUnitConfigIndex.description: The unit number of an entry.

bayStackUnitConfigRearPortAdminMode.name: bayStackUnitConfigRearPortAdminMode
bayStackUnitConfigRearPortAdminMode.description: The current administrative rear-port mode for this unit. This value will be applied at the next stack re-boot if it is different from the current operational value. Supported values are: standalone (rear-port mode is enabled normal), stacking (rear-port mode is disabled) and spb(rear-port mode is enabled with loopback port reserved).

bayStackUnitConfigRearPortOperMode.name: bayStackUnitConfigRearPortOperMode
bayStackUnitConfigRearPortOperMode.description: The current operational rear-port mode for this unit. Supported values are: standalone (operational rear-port mode is enabled normal), stacking (operational rear-port mode is disabled) and spb(operational rear-port mode is enabled with loopback port reserved).
